\section*{SECTION A}

Answer THREE questions from this section
1. (a) Explain three reasons for earthing an electrical installation.
(b) Outline four methods used to achieve earthing.
(c) Define the following terms as used in electrical protection:
(i) current rating;
(ii) discrimination.
(d) Draw a labelled diagram of cartridge fuse.
2. (a) (i) State four causes of accidents in the workshop.
(ii) Outline the procedure to be followed incase of a fire outbreak.
(b) Explain the function of each of the following workshop tools and state how they are stored:
(i) hacksaw:
(ii) soldering bit;
(iii) centre punch.
(c) Explain the following methods of battery charging:
(i) trickle charging;
(ii) constant current.
(d) A battery whose terminal voltage is $12 \mathrm{~V} \mathrm{d.c}$ and internal resistance $0.25 \Omega$ is charged from a 14 V d.c supply.
Calculate the charging current.
3. (a) (i) List four types of electric bells.
(ii) Ourline three IEE regulation requirements regarding bell transformers.
(b) Draw the following electrical bell indicator types:
(i) pendulum type;
(ii) mechanical replacement.
(c) Explain why the following installation tests are carried out and for each case state the measuring instrument used:
(i) continuity test.
(ii) earthing test.
(d) Illustrate the measurement of power, current and voltage in the same circuit.
4. (a) State three IEE regulation requirements regarding:
(i) switch gears;
(ii) 13 A socket outlets.
(b) Draw a three heat switch showing the following positions:
(i) low;
(ii) medium.
(c) (i) Outline three factors to be considered when selecting the site for a diesel power station;
(ii) Draw a labelled block diagram of a diesel power station.
5. (a) (i) State two IEE regulation requirements regarding cable joints and terminations.
(ii) Define the term soldering.
(b) Sketch the following cable joints and for each case state one application:
(i) Britannia joint;
(ii) Belhanger's joint.
(c) (i) Outline four precautions to be observed when installing catenary wiring system.
(ii) Describe the earth concentric wiring system.
(d) Draw a labelled diagram showing a vertical bus-bar rising main system.

