\section*{Answer TWO questions from this section}
6. (a) (i) Explain the function of a solar collector.
(ii) Name three types of solar energy collectors.
(b) With aid of a labelled diagram explain the operation of solar concentrating type cookers.
(c) Outline two advantages and two disadvantages of using solar electricity.
(d) With aid of a labelled diagram explain the operation of a solar cell.
7. (a) Describe the following as used in a solar installation:
(i) consumer unit;
(ii) ceiling roses.
(b) Draw the wiring diagram of a photo-voltaic (PV) solar installation control gear/equipment in the correct sequence.
(c) Explain two benefits of solar electric energy in the remote areas.
(d) A solar module is rated 40 wp , current 3.2 A and output voltage of 17.6 V . Draw the connections and show the outputs if two of such modules are connected in:
(i) series;
(ii) parallel.
8. (a) Outine the service and maintenance done on a photo-voltaic (PV) solar module.
(b) (i) Explain three ways a solar battery needs service.
(ii) Outline the safety precautions when handling lead-acid batteries.
(c) Explain each of the following factors when sizing and designing a P.V solar installation:
(i) insolation;
(ii) system losses.
(d) A 12 V d.c P.V solar home system whose total daily energy demand is 1200 wh. Assuming that the system losses are $20 \%$, determine:
(i) total daily system requirements;
(ii) battery capacity in ampere hours.

